This paper deals with termination criteria for rewriting systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions the Calculus of Constructions, which is a type theory used in programming language research, placing it under Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also deals with dependent types, which are a topic in both Type Theory (cs.IT) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions beta-reduction, which is a fundamental concept in Computational Linguistics (cs.CL).
